<item>
            <title>[LANG-826] FastDateParser does not handle non-ASCII digits correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-826</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The FastDateParser class assumes that all numbers are ascii digits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, that is not the case for some locales such as&lt;br/&gt;
ja_JP_JP, hi_IN, th_TH, and th_TH_TH&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rather than using &quot;\d&quot;, the code needs to match using &quot;\p&lt;/p&gt;
{IsNd}
&lt;p&gt;&quot; which is the Unicode class for numeric digits.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
